lead_paragraph: Malik Monk scored 34 points, Isaiah Briscoe had a triple-double and No. 8 Kentucky bounced back impressively from a loss at Louisville with a 99-76 victory over Mississippi on Thursday night in the SEC opener for both teams.

headline.print_headline: No. 8 Kentucky Bounces Back, Beats Mississippi 99-76
